85
00:07:04,717 --> 00:07:06,521
That hurt me.

86
00:07:08,687 --> 00:07:10,777
If it's that annoying,

87
00:07:10,777 --> 00:07:12,867
you can just ignore me.

88
00:07:12,867 --> 00:07:13,947
What?

89
00:07:13,947 --> 00:07:18,317
You could have just ignored it, but why did you have to make up a team dinner that didn't exist?

90
00:07:18,317 --> 00:07:19,857
Right,

91
00:07:19,857 --> 00:07:23,917
there was a reason why you said something about my phone.

92
00:07:23,917 --> 00:07:27,937
- Seo Jae Yun.
- This is my private life.

93
00:07:27,937 --> 00:07:30,397
Have you never thought that you're just being nosy?

94
00:07:30,397 --> 00:07:31,937
- Nosy?
- Yes!

95
00:07:31,937 --> 00:07:33,802
What bothers you so much?

96
00:07:33,802 --> 00:07:36,577
Why are you doing this to me?

97
00:07:39,117 --> 00:07:41,278
I'll get going now.

98
00:07:43,337 --> 00:07:45,737
If you go like this now,

99
00:07:45,737 --> 00:07:49,927
I'm never going to be involved in your life ever again.

100
00:07:49,927 --> 00:07:52,472
We'll only be the team leader and the employee,

101
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:54,690
only that shell of a relationship will remain.

102
00:07:54,690 --> 00:08:00,440
♫ We have to get distant so that we don't cry anymore ♫

103
00:08:00,440 --> 00:08:06,210
♫ Now run away, so far away ♫

104
00:08:06,210 --> 00:08:09,600
♫ Even if I lose you forever ♫

105
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:11,323
I'll get off...

106
00:08:13,567 --> 00:08:15,990
I'll get off from work.

107
00:08:15,990 --> 00:08:20,800
♫ Will you send me away even if it hurts? ♫

108
00:08:21,620 --> 00:08:27,450
♫ Now run away, so far away ♫

109
00:08:27,450 --> 00:08:33,880
♫ Slowly, I'll leave for you ♫

110
00:08:47,297 --> 00:08:49,737
Seung Seok, what happened to your face?

111
00:08:49,737 --> 00:08:51,137
What's going on?

112
00:08:51,137 --> 00:08:53,269
What's your relationship with him?

113
00:08:54,107 --> 00:08:56,847
- I'm...
- He's my friend.

114
00:08:56,847 --> 00:08:59,767
Yes, I'm his friend.

115
00:08:59,767 --> 00:09:01,927
This bastard is a total crook.

116
00:09:01,927 --> 00:09:04,907
I mean, it was beyond frustrating, and that's why I hit him just once.

117
00:09:04,907 --> 00:09:07,807
Just once? Does this look like I got hit just once?

118
00:09:07,807 --> 00:09:12,137
This punk... You scammed my innocent mother first!

119
00:09:12,137 --> 00:09:14,407
Hey, Mr. Customer's Son!

120
00:09:14,407 --> 00:09:19,617
I told her multiple times that the mats were not refundable!

121
00:09:19,617 --> 00:09:22,217
Understood? It's written here on the contract as well!

122
00:09:22,217 --> 00:09:23,737
Please calm down, Sir.

123
00:09:23,737 --> 00:09:29,037
How can he sell 20 mats to an older person who can't even hear that well?

124
00:09:29,037 --> 00:09:31,467
Mom! Did you hear anything from this guy?

125
00:09:31,467 --> 00:09:32,780
What?

126
00:09:32,780 --> 00:09:34,227
I can't hear you.

127
00:09:34,227 --> 00:09:38,107
See? Also, this is not my mother's signature!

128
00:09:38,107 --> 00:09:40,907
How dare you think I'm such a pushover. I'm going to sue you!

129
00:09:40,907 --> 00:09:44,018
Sir, please keep it down.

130
00:09:45,380 --> 00:09:48,630
Mr. Yu Seung Seok, why don't you tell me?

131
00:09:48,630 --> 00:09:51,807
First of all, who signed this contract?

132
00:09:51,807 --> 00:09:55,587
Well... I did sign that contract.

133
00:09:55,587 --> 00:09:57,431
See?

134
00:09:57,431 --> 00:09:59,439
What I told you is correct!

135
00:10:00,893 --> 00:10:04,383
[Police Station]

136
00:10:08,647 --> 00:10:10,877
I think it's good that you decided to settle.

137
00:10:10,877 --> 00:10:13,507
I let it slide this time. Young man, you need to live a better life!

138
00:10:13,507 --> 00:10:16,435
- Please, stop it!
- Okay, all right.

139
00:10:17,217 --> 00:10:18,368
Let's go get some nice food.

140
00:10:18,368 --> 00:10:19,833
Have a good night.

141
00:10:33,007 --> 00:10:35,877
I'm sorry. I owe you this.

142
00:10:35,877 --> 00:10:38,249
I didn't call you to do this.

143
00:10:41,347 --> 00:10:43,467
I'll pay you back the settlement money as soon as possible.

144
00:10:45,867 --> 00:10:47,667
Seung Seok.

145
00:10:47,667 --> 00:10:48,965
Yes?

146
00:10:49,687 --> 00:10:51,467
Let's have a talk.

147
00:11:01,377 --> 00:11:03,276
What do you want to talk about?

148
00:11:06,887 --> 00:11:08,467
Seung Seok.

149
00:11:09,377 --> 00:11:12,959
Remember when we used to hand out flyers as a part-time job in high school?

150
00:11:13,882 --> 00:11:16,175
Of course, I remember that.

151
00:11:16,175 --> 00:11:18,059
Why are you talking about it all of a sudden?

152
00:11:19,429 --> 00:11:25,577
We worked really hard, even though our hourly wage was low.

153
00:11:25,577 --> 00:11:30,407
We stopped busily walking people and said, "Please take this just once, Nuna."

154
00:11:30,407 --> 00:11:33,097
We acted cutesy and stuff.

155
00:11:33,097 --> 00:11:34,607
So our boss really liked us.

156
00:11:34,607 --> 00:11:36,952
What are you trying to say?

157
00:11:40,567 --> 00:11:43,257
Can't you quit your work and do something else?

158
00:11:43,257 --> 00:11:44,495
What?

159
00:11:45,427 --> 00:11:49,877
It's hard to raise the sales record and deal with people.

160
00:11:49,877 --> 00:11:53,454
Jae Yun. I heard that I have a talent for it.

161
00:11:54,339 --> 00:11:57,175
If I sell a bit more, I'll reach the Sapphire Level.

162
00:11:57,175 --> 00:12:00,987
Then I'll get money in my bank account without making sales! When that time comes─

163
00:12:00,987 --> 00:12:02,491
But...

164
00:12:03,353 --> 00:12:06,119
Don't you think this is not okay?

165
00:12:06,877 --> 00:12:09,527
What's not okay?

166
00:12:09,527 --> 00:12:11,597
Just everything what happened today.

167
00:12:11,597 --> 00:12:13,174
Hey...

168
00:12:13,817 --> 00:12:16,137
all of that was a misunderstanding.

169
00:12:16,137 --> 00:12:18,655
You also saw it. It's just that people misunderstood things─

170
00:12:18,655 --> 00:12:21,319
I bought a lot for you until now!

171
00:12:22,767 --> 00:12:25,547
Seung Seok, if you did this much─

172
00:12:25,547 --> 00:12:27,335
You bought it "for me?"

173
00:12:29,547 --> 00:12:31,198
Hey, Seo Jae Yun.

174
00:12:31,198 --> 00:12:33,266
Are you also despising me now?

175
00:12:34,857 --> 00:12:37,457
It's funny now that I think about it.

176
00:12:37,457 --> 00:12:39,407
Tell me honestly.

177
00:12:40,587 --> 00:12:43,087
You are also embarrassed by me, aren't you?

178
00:12:43,087 --> 00:12:45,758
Why are you trying to lecture me all of a sudden?

179
00:12:45,758 --> 00:12:46,975
Why?

180
00:12:46,975 --> 00:12:50,417
Do you feel like you are something now since you became a landlord and are collecting rent money?

181
00:12:51,267 --> 00:12:52,534
Sure.

182
00:12:53,356 --> 00:12:57,457
You did buy a lot for me. I know that and am thankful for that.

183
00:12:57,457 --> 00:13:02,908
But I'm the one who thought of you, you know?

184
00:13:02,908 --> 00:13:07,683
I shared the things with you because those are good things. I wanted my friend to use good things!

185
00:13:08,907 --> 00:13:15,201
Wow, I'm hearing such nonsense in my life.

186
00:13:18,607 --> 00:13:20,093
Seung Seok.

187
00:13:23,078 --> 00:13:25,385
Are we really friends?

188
00:13:26,387 --> 00:13:28,893
What the heck are you saying now?

189
00:13:58,167 --> 00:14:00,215
It's been a while.

190
00:14:00,215 --> 00:14:03,343
Hey, thanks for coming.

191
00:14:03,343 --> 00:14:05,900
Why is it so hard to see you these days?

192
00:14:06,637 --> 00:14:08,497
There's no particular reason.

193
00:14:10,717 --> 00:14:12,685
I was busy with work.

194
00:14:13,517 --> 00:14:15,967
Are you dating someone?

195
00:14:16,677 --> 00:14:18,481
No, it's not like that.

196
00:14:19,234 --> 00:14:23,835
I can't get used to you not having someone next to you.

197
00:14:25,077 --> 00:14:26,177
What do you want to drink?

198
00:14:26,177 --> 00:14:28,137
It's on me.

199
00:14:28,137 --> 00:14:31,887
Do they sell soju bombs here?

200
00:14:31,887 --> 00:14:35,137
Hey, how can you look for a soju bomb here?

201
00:14:35,137 --> 00:14:36,922
Are you out of your mind?

202
00:14:37,794 --> 00:14:40,904
I already have a glass of whiskey I'm drinking.

203
00:14:55,027 --> 00:14:57,100
There's something going on with you.

204
00:14:58,477 --> 00:14:59,900
What about it?

205
00:14:59,900 --> 00:15:00,850
Hey,

206
00:15:00,858 --> 00:15:03,421
do you know how many employees I have in my company?

207
00:15:03,421 --> 00:15:06,091
I can tell that just by looking at your face.

208
00:15:07,047 --> 00:15:09,574
You are amazing indeed.

209
00:15:10,767 --> 00:15:12,547
What's going on?

210
00:15:12,547 --> 00:15:14,582
You can tell me about it.

211
00:15:17,668 --> 00:15:21,904
It just bothers me.

212
00:15:22,617 --> 00:15:23,972
What?

213
00:15:27,037 --> 00:15:28,917
I mean...

214
00:15:30,157 --> 00:15:34,040
There's a really frustrating person that I know.

215
00:15:35,057 --> 00:15:37,246
I really can't understand that person.

216
00:15:39,017 --> 00:15:42,150
That person doesn't spend any money on themselves,

217
00:15:42,150 --> 00:15:44,964
but they just give everything to other people.

218
00:15:45,945 --> 00:15:51,428
It's just so absurd that it makes me angry when I look at that person.

219
00:15:52,977 --> 00:15:54,412
But besides that,

220
00:15:54,412 --> 00:15:57,165
that person is a great person.

221
00:15:57,165 --> 00:16:00,877
A smart and hard-working person.

222
00:16:02,007 --> 00:16:04,554
Also, pretty good-looking.

223
00:16:05,923 --> 00:16:09,802
So when I pull pranks on them,

224
00:16:09,802 --> 00:16:12,000
their reaction is very funny.

225
00:16:13,297 --> 00:16:15,419
So I want to keep making jokes around them.

226
00:16:15,419 --> 00:16:20,777
Either complimenting or talking bad about them, can you just do one thing?

227
00:16:20,777 --> 00:16:22,997
Oh, Ji Ho Jun.

228
00:16:22,997 --> 00:16:24,419
Why?

229
00:16:25,057 --> 00:16:27,387
You totally fell for that person.

230
00:16:27,387 --> 00:16:28,817
What are you talking about?

231
00:16:28,817 --> 00:16:29,820
It's clear that you have feelings for that person.

232
00:16:29,820 --> 00:16:31,288
Feelings...

233
00:16:34,317 --> 00:16:36,347
Hey, it's not like that.

234
00:16:36,347 --> 00:16:38,627
It doesn't make any sense.

235
00:16:38,627 --> 00:16:41,407
It's total nonsense. What are you talking about?

236
00:16:44,347 --> 00:16:45,964
Right.

237
00:16:45,964 --> 00:16:47,447
Why was I like that?

238
00:16:47,447 --> 00:16:49,428
- What?
- What?

239
00:16:50,327 --> 00:16:51,634
It's nothing.

240
00:16:55,607 --> 00:16:57,420
I can't do that.

241
00:16:58,317 --> 00:17:00,987
