242
00:17:00,987 --> 00:17:03,767
You don't have to care about that person living like that or not.

243
00:17:03,767 --> 00:17:07,468
When did you care about other people that much anyway?

244
00:17:32,767 --> 00:17:34,942
Stop being a pushover!

245
00:17:34,942 --> 00:17:37,513
It's annoying to see that from the side.

246
00:17:40,307 --> 00:17:42,460
What does it matter to you?

247
00:17:47,917 --> 00:17:49,817
Manager Choi.

248
00:17:49,817 --> 00:17:52,029
Aren't you cold?

249
00:17:52,029 --> 00:17:53,947
I keep getting goosebumps!

250
00:17:53,947 --> 00:17:58,881
Me, too. Why is it so cold when all the windows are closed?

251
00:18:30,327 --> 00:18:31,980
Team Leader.

252
00:18:32,637 --> 00:18:34,098
Documents to sign─

253
00:18:34,098 --> 00:18:35,715
You can leave them there.

254
00:18:42,707 --> 00:18:45,827
Do you have something to say?

255
00:18:47,057 --> 00:18:49,203
If you go like this now!

256
00:18:50,755 --> 00:18:54,757
I'm never going to be involved in your life ever again.

257
00:18:54,757 --> 00:18:57,181
We'll only be the team leader and the employee,

258
00:18:57,181 --> 00:19:00,137
only that shell of a relationship will remain.

259
00:19:00,137 --> 00:19:04,487
You don't feel the aftermath of the decision at that moment.

260
00:19:04,487 --> 00:19:06,877
Because it always comes a second later.

261
00:19:06,877 --> 00:19:08,509
Do you have something to say?

262
00:19:11,417 --> 00:19:13,301
No, I don't have anything.

263
00:19:30,336 --> 00:19:31,990
Yes, Department Head.

